My Role in the Project
I was responsible for the Kiosk Booking Flow and Advanced Pricing & Add-ons modules. My work focused on creating a seamless 7-screen self-service kiosk experience for guests, implementing dynamic pricing strategies, and enabling guests to add optional amenities to their stay.
My Contributions
1. Kiosk 7-Screen Flow
•	Built the complete guest journey from Welcome to Confirmation
•	Created controllers for all 7 screens: SearchController, RoomSelectionController, AddOnsController, LoyaltyController, SummaryController, ConfirmationController
•	Implemented data passing between screens using a custom BookingData class
•	Connected all FXML files with their respective controllers
2. Strategy Pattern (Pricing)
•	Implemented PricingStrategy interface with three concrete strategies:
o	StandardPricing - Weekday rates
o	WeekendPricing - 20% surcharge for weekend stays
o	PeakSeasonPricing - 30% surcharge for peak season (July, August, December)
•	Integrated dynamic pricing into the Summary screen
3. Decorator Pattern (Dynamic Amenities - MS3)
•	Created BillComponent interface as the core component
•	Implemented BaseBill to wrap room costs
•	Created decorators for each amenity:
o	WiFiDecorator - $10 per night per device
o	BreakfastDecorator - $15 per person per day
o	ShuttleDecorator - $35 per trip
o	SpaDecorator - $50 per session
•	The decorators chain together to build the final bill dynamically


Challenges I Faced
Challenge 1: Null Pointer Exceptions with Spinners
Problem: When trying to save add-ons, the spinner values were returning null, causing NullPointerException. The console showed spinner value=null even when the checkbox was selected.
Solution: I discovered that setupSpinners() was being called AFTER loadExistingData(). The spinners didn't have their value factories created yet when loadExistingData() tried to set their values. I reordered the method calls in setMainController() to create spinners first, then load data. I also added null safety checks.
Challenge 2: FXML Controller Binding
Problem: The CONTINUE button on the Search screen wasn't working. Clicking it did nothing.
Solution: I found that the fx:controller attribute in the FXML file was pointing to UIControllerinstead of SearchController. After correcting it to SearchController, the button started working. This taught me the importance of matching FXML controller references.
Challenge 3: Add-ons Not Adding to Total
Problem: When users selected add-ons, the quantity remained at 0, so no cost was added to the bill.
Solution: I updated the setupCheckboxListeners() method to automatically set the spinner quantity to 1 when a checkbox is selected. This ensured that if a user checks an amenity, they get at least one unit by default.
Challenge 4: Navigation Between Screens
Problem: The setMainController method wasn't being called on child controllers, so mainController was always null.
Solution: I implemented the switchScene() method in UIController to use reflection to find and call setMainController on any controller that has it. This ensured proper parent-child controller communication.

